1.) First from my home, I cd into desktop and then cd into tz which was the copy of the repo folder sitting on my desktop.

harrisdoan@s-164-67-81-219 ~ % cd Desktop
harrisdoan@s-164-67-81-219 Desktop % cd tz
harrisdoan@s-164-67-81-219 tz % ls

2.) Then I can do a grep expression to find exactly when that instance occured in the repo:

grep -n "Even newspaper reports present contradictory information." *

The space at the end of the star is very important. Can't forget that

3.) From then it produced this result:

harrisdoan@s-164-67-81-219 tz % grep -n "Even newspaper reports present contradictory information." *
northamerica:900:# and wrote "Even newspaper reports present contradictory information."


4.) Now with a name and number, I can use the command git blame to find more on this specific commit.

git blame -L 900 northamerica


