617ecc28d (Arthur David Olson 2010-12-09 20:07:45 -0500  565) # and indicates that standard time was adopted effective noon, January
617ecc28d (Arthur David Olson 2010-12-09 20:07:45 -0500  566) # 13, 1896 (page 218), that in "1933, the Legislature decreed daylight
617ecc28d (Arthur David Olson 2010-12-09 20:07:45 -0500  567) # saving for the period between the last Sunday of each April and the
617ecc28d (Arthur David Olson 2010-12-09 20:07:45 -0500  568) # last Sunday of each September, but less than a month later repealed the
617ecc28d (Arthur David Olson 2010-12-09 20:07:45 -0500  569) # act," (page 220), that year-round daylight saving time was in effect
617ecc28d (Arthur David Olson 2010-12-09 20:07:45 -0500  570) # from 1942-02-09 to 1945-09-30 (page 221, with no time of day given for
617ecc28d (Arthur David Olson 2010-12-09 20:07:45 -0500  571) # when clocks changed) and that clocks were changed by 30 minutes
617ecc28d (Arthur David Olson 2010-12-09 20:07:45 -0500  572) # effective the second Sunday of June, 1947 (page 219, with no time of
5a453c138 (Arthur David Olson 2010-12-16 16:58:31 -0500  573) # day given for when clocks changed). A footnote for the 1933 changes
5a453c138 (Arthur David Olson 2010-12-16 16:58:31 -0500  574) # cites Session Laws of Hawaii 1933, "Act. 90 (approved 26 Apr. 1933)
b2cef0068 (Arthur David Olson 2011-01-19 14:16:52 -0500  575) # and Act 163 (approved 21 May 1933)."
