131ad475e (Arthur David Olson 2003-03-24 09:30:03 -0500  613) # Between 1944-01-01 and 1944-04-01 the State of Arizona used standard
131ad475e (Arthur David Olson 2003-03-24 09:30:03 -0500  614) # time, but by federal law railroads, airlines, bus lines, military
131ad475e (Arthur David Olson 2003-03-24 09:30:03 -0500  615) # personnel, and some engaged in interstate commerce continued to
131ad475e (Arthur David Olson 2003-03-24 09:30:03 -0500  616) # observe war (i.e., daylight saving) time.  The 1944-03-17 Phoenix
131ad475e (Arthur David Olson 2003-03-24 09:30:03 -0500  617) # Gazette says that was the date the law changed, and that 04-01 was
131ad475e (Arthur David Olson 2003-03-24 09:30:03 -0500  618) # the date the state's clocks would change.  In 1945 the State of
131ad475e (Arthur David Olson 2003-03-24 09:30:03 -0500  619) # Arizona used standard time all year, again with exceptions only as
131ad475e (Arthur David Olson 2003-03-24 09:30:03 -0500  620) # mandated by federal law.  Arizona observed DST in 1967, but Arizona
131ad475e (Arthur David Olson 2003-03-24 09:30:03 -0500  621) # Laws 1968, ch. 183 (effective 1968-03-21) repealed DST.
